text: Laconia is a city in Belknap County, New Hampshire, United States. The population was 16,871 at the 2020 census. It is the county seat of Belknap County. Laconia is between Lake Winnipesaukee and Winnisquam Lake, includes the neighborhoods of Lakeport and Weirs Beach. == References == Category:19th- century establishments in New Hampshire Category:1855 establishments in the United States Category:Cities in New Hampshire Category:County seats in New Hampshire
